# Gameplay UI test identifiers

Phased plan: [`docs/testing/x01-cricket-ui-test-phased-plan.md`](../../docs/testing/x01-cricket-ui-test-phased-plan.md)

Identifiers are the **public contract** between SwiftUI and `Tests/UI`. Prefer identifiers over visible copy in tests.

## Pad keys (use `ScoringPadKey` / `ScoringPadIconKey`)

| Mode | Pattern | Examples |
|------|---------|----------|
| X01 | `pad_{segment}` | `pad_20`, `pad_0` (miss), `pad_25`, `pad_double`, `pad_triple`, `pad_undo` |
| Visual board | `board_*` | `board_input_root`, `board_miss`, `board_undo`, `board_enter`, `board_visit_preview`, header toggle `match_dartEntryPresentationToggle` |
| Cricket | `cricket_{segment}` | `cricket_20`…`cricket_15`, `cricket_bull`, `cricket_miss`, `cricket_double`, `cricket_triple`, `cricket_undo`, `cricket_enter` |

Every pad variant (compact, landscape wide, accessibility) must expose the **same** identifiers.

## Board landmarks

| Element | Identifier |
|---------|------------|
| Active X01 card | `scoreCard_active` (inactive: `scoreCard`) — combined label, `children: .ignore` |
| Active Cricket column | `cricket_column_active` (`cricket_column`) |
| Match exit | `match_exit` |
| X01 config summary | `x01_match_config_summary` |
| Cricket subtitle | `cricket_match_subtitle` |

## Setup (Play home)

`startMatchButton`, `resumeMatchButton`, `setup_changeModeButton`, `setup_selected_{name}`, `setup_*Chip`, `setup_*Option_*`, `select_{name}`.

## Summary

`matchSummaryHeader`, `matchSummaryRematch`, `matchSummaryDone`, `matchSummaryUndoLastThrowWarning`.

## Rules when changing UI

1. **Do not rename** identifiers without updating helpers + WCAG tests in the same PR.
2. New interactive control → add identifier before merging; wire WCAG `assertInteractiveElement` if user-facing.
3. Hidden decorative nodes: `accessibilityHidden(true)` OK; banners that tests must query keep an identifier even if hidden from VoiceOver.
4. Header undo: prefer `match_undo` (gap today — tests use `pad_undo` only).
5. Board state: assert via **combined column/card label** (`Closed`, MPR, visit totals), not per-cell IDs unless adding a dedicated contract.

## Layout changes

See [`gameplay-layout-size-classes.mdc`](gameplay-layout-size-classes.mdc). Landscape UI tests target **iPhone Pro Max** (regular horizontal size class on phone idiom).
